insurance division he served in various senior management positions at the charter company from  to  his professional experience also includes time spent with the environmental recovery group koger properties business valuation inc he served as financial adviser of environmental recovery  group he served as an executive vice president of koger properties he served as a principal of business valuation inc since january  he served as a director of special projects at pic n save since december  he served as a senior adviser to business valuation at heritage capital group inc since  mr serkin has been the chairman of heritage capital group inc since  he serves as a cochairman at genesis rehabilitation hospital inc he served as cochairman of genesis health inc until december   he has been vice chairman of genesis health inc since december   he has been vice chairman and independent director for consolidatedtomoka land co since may   and february  respectively he serves as a director of planeths llc he serves as a director at genesis health inc formerly brooks rehabilitation inc he served as a director of koger properties he is a member of the financial executives institute the association for corporate growth and an honorary member of beta gamma sigma he serves as an executive professor at the university of north florida’s college of business administration and has lectured at jacksonville university’s college of business administration the indian institute of management in bangalore india the university of the south pacific in fiji and the harvard business school mr serkin in addition to his teaching and lecturing experiences as the executiveinresidence and a visiting professor at the university of north floridas college of business administration he lectures extensively on a number of financial topics including corporate turnarounds mergers and acquisitions business valuations financial restructurings and bankruptcy mr serkin is committed to his community and has served in leadership positions on numerous civic boards and activities including the unf foundation museum of contemporary art museum of science and history governors economic advisory council leadership jacksonville and youth leadership jacksonville cultural council downtown vision baptist medical centerbeaches art with a heart jcci community foundation finance committee jacksonville marine institute and associated marine institute mimi and lee adams environmental advisory board sheriffs advisory council first coast venture capital group enterprise north florida river club community coaches program united way jacksonville chamber of commerce big brothers and big sisters mental health resource center junior achievement unf business advisory council unf financing corporation fccj open campus advisory board and downtown master plan committee in  leadership jacksonville honored mr serkin with its distinguished community trustee award he served a four year tour of active duty as a lieutenant in the u s navy assigned to nuclear submarines and deep submergence rescue and salvage projects mr serkin received his bs in engineering from georgia tech in  he also went on to earn his ms in engineering and in  received his mba in finance from harvard business school he has pursued postgraduate studies at oxford university cambridge university and the london school of economicsread full background corporate headquarters  beach boulevardjacksonville florida united statesphone fax  board members memberships chairman and principalheritage capital group inccochairmangenesis rehabilitation hospital incvice chairmangenesis health incdirectorplaneths llcpresentvicechairman consolidatedtomoka land co education ms harvard business schoolmba harvard business schoolmasters degree university of cambridgebs georgia institute of technologymasters degree the london school of economics and political sciencemasters degree university of oxford other affiliations consolidatedtomoka land coharvard busines